&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 2 Part Time (30 hours) Position available&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;FIXED TERM/SECONDMENT 5 months until March 2021&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Interview date 24/11/2020 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a flexible member of staff to join our Care Home Support Team (CHST) to undertake phlebotomy and support with administration. The CHST is a small multidisciplinary team that was set up earlier this year to offer support to Care Home Staff and proactively undertake review of residents to help prevent unplanned avoidable admissions to hospital. As part of the team’s development we are now working with Primary Care to undertake Comprehensive Geriatric Assessments on all Care Home Residents. A pivotal part of this assessment process is the completion of blood tests to support medication reviews.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the first instance the role is fixed term but there is potential for the role to become substantive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For Further Information please contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emma Glover: Care Home Support Team Lead 01983 822099 extension 3141.&lt;/p&gt;
